### 3.2 IMU prefilter path (driver â†’ EKF)

`VehicleIMU` (`src/modules/sensors/vehicle_imu/`) calibrates (scale/offset/rotation) and **integrates** over the `IMU_INTEG_RATE` window (default 200 Hz) with a coning-corrected integrator, publishing `vehicle_imu.{delta_angle, delta_velocity}`. **No LPF/notch on this path** â€” the notched/LPF'd `vehicle_angular_velocity` / `vehicle_acceleration` are for the *controllers*. The integrated deltas drive prediction directly:

$$
\delta\boldsymbol\theta \approx \int \boldsymbol\omega_{\mathrm{body}}\,dt \;(\mathrm{rad}),\qquad
\delta\mathbf v \approx \int \mathbf a_{\mathrm{body}}\,dt \;(\mathrm{m/s},\ \text{gravity included}).
$$

### 3.3 Time alignment, down-sampling & buffering

Each non-IMU sample is **time-shifted backward** before buffering so its timestamp lands on the EKF's delayed fusion horizon (`estimator_interface.cpp:123/159/238`):

$$
t_{\mathrm{buf}} = t_{\mathrm{sample}} \;-\; \underbrace{\texttt{EKF2\_<S>\_DELAY}\cdot10^3}_{\mu s}\;-\;\tfrac12\,\overline{\Delta t}_{\mathrm{ekf}} .
$$

A minimum interval $\Delta t_{\min}^{\mathrm{obs}} = (t_{\mathrm{imu,now}}-t_{\mathrm{delayed}})/(L_{\mathrm{obs}}-1)$ rate-limits each buffer so no sample is overwritten before the horizon reaches it (`:97`).

The **IMU down-sampler** (`imu_down_sampler.cpp:13`) accumulates fast IMU samples to the filter rate set by `EKF2_PREDICT_US` (10 000 Âµs â†’ 100 Hz):

$$
\mathbf q_{\mathrm{acc}} \leftarrow \mathbf q_{\mathrm{acc}} \otimes \Delta\mathbf q(\delta\boldsymbol\theta),\qquad
\delta\mathbf v_{\mathrm{acc}} \leftarrow \mathbf R(\Delta\mathbf q)^{-1}\delta\mathbf v_{\mathrm{acc}} + \tfrac12\!\left(\delta\mathbf v + \mathbf R(\Delta\mathbf q)^{-1}\delta\mathbf v\right),
$$

triggering when the accumulated count/time reaches the target. On trigger the sample is pushed to `_imu_buffer`; `_time_delayed_us` (oldest IMU) is the **fusion horizon**, and $\overline{\Delta t}_{\mathrm{ekf}}=$`_dt_ekf_avg` is the slewed step (`ekf.cpp:293`). The **output predictor** instead runs on *every* full-rate IMU sample inside `setIMUData()` (`:83`).

