## 4. The 24-state vector

`stateSample` (`common.h:269`); symbolic names from `EKF/python/ekf_derivation/derivation.py:39`. Covariance $\mathbf P\in\mathbb{R}^{24\times24}$ is symmetric.

| Idx | Symbol | `stateSample` member | Meaning | Units |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 0â€“3 | $q_0\,q_1\,q_2\,q_3$ | `quat_nominal` | rotation **body â†’ earth** (NED) | â€“ |
| 4â€“6 | $v_x\,v_y\,v_z$ | `vel` | velocity, earth NED | m/s |
| 7â€“9 | $p_x\,p_y\,p_z$ | `pos` | position, earth NED ($z$ = down) | m |
| 10â€“12 | $b_{\delta\theta,x/y/z}$ | `delta_ang_bias` | **delta-angle** (gyro) bias | rad |
| 13â€“15 | $b_{\delta v,x/y/z}$ | `delta_vel_bias` | **delta-velocity** (accel) bias | m/s |
| 16â€“18 | $i_x\,i_y\,i_z$ | `mag_I` | earth magnetic field, NED | gauss |
| 19â€“21 | $i_{bx}\,i_{by}\,i_{bz}$ | `mag_B` | magnetometer bias, body | gauss |
| 22â€“23 | $w_x\,w_y$ | `wind_vel` | horizontal wind, earth NE | m/s |

> **Delta biases, not rate biases.** States 10â€“15 bias the *integrated* IMU increments over one sample, so the equivalent rate/accel bias is $\mathbf b_{\delta\theta}/\Delta t$ and $\mathbf b_{\delta v}/\Delta t$. `Ekf::fuse` (`ekf_helper.cpp:789`) applies a gain slice per group: $\mathbf q\!-\!=\!\mathbf K_{0:4}y$, $\mathbf v\!-\!=\!\mathbf K_{4:7}y$, $\mathbf p\!-\!=\!\mathbf K_{7:10}y$, $\mathbf b_{\delta\theta}\!-\!=\!\mathbf K_{10:13}y$, $\mathbf b_{\delta v}\!-\!=\!\mathbf K_{13:16}y$, $\mathbf m_I\!-\!=\!\mathbf K_{16:19}y$, $\mathbf m_B\!-\!=\!\mathbf K_{19:22}y$, $\mathbf w\!-\!=\!\mathbf K_{22:24}y$. The indices above *are* the covariance indices.

