## 5. EKF update cycle

![EKF2 update cycle and R/Q hooks](ekf2_estimator_pipeline_2026-05-25_cycle.svg){width=100%}

`Ekf::update()` (`ekf.cpp:158`) runs once per down-sampled IMU sample, in order **predictCovariance â†’ predictState â†’ controlFusionModes â†’ correctOutputStates**.

### 5.1 State prediction â€” strapdown INS (`predictState`, `ekf.cpp:253`)

$$
\begin{aligned}
\delta\boldsymbol\theta_c &= \delta\boldsymbol\theta - \mathbf b_{\delta\theta} - \mathbf R^\top\boldsymbol\omega_{\mathrm{earth}}\,\Delta t && \text{(gyro bias + earth-rotation removed)}\\
\mathbf q &\leftarrow \big(\mathbf q \otimes \Delta\mathbf q(\delta\boldsymbol\theta_c)\big)\big/\lVert\cdot\rVert,\quad \mathbf R=\mathbf R(\mathbf q)\\
\mathbf v &\leftarrow \mathbf v + \mathbf R(\delta\mathbf v - \mathbf b_{\delta v}) ,\qquad v_z \leftarrow v_z + g\,\Delta t\\
\mathbf p &\leftarrow \mathbf p + \tfrac12(\mathbf v_{\mathrm{old}}+\mathbf v)\,\Delta t && \text{(trapezoidal)}
\end{aligned}
$$

with $\Delta\mathbf q(\boldsymbol\phi)=\big[1,\ \tfrac12\boldsymbol\phi^\top\big]^\top$ (the small-angle increment used in the derivation, `derivation.py:94`). Bias/mag/wind states are unchanged by prediction. The step is slewed: $\overline{\Delta t}_{\mathrm{ekf}}\leftarrow0.99\,\overline{\Delta t}_{\mathrm{ekf}}+0.01\,\mathrm{clamp}\!\big(\tfrac12(\delta\theta_{dt}+\delta v_{dt})\big)$.

### 5.2 Covariance prediction, the state-transition matrix $\mathbf A$, and process noise $\mathbf Q$

The propagation (`covariance.cpp:102`, symbolic `derivation.py:72`, compiled `predict_covariance.h`, "Total ops: 2887") is

$$
\boxed{\ \mathbf P^- = \mathbf A\,\mathbf P\,\mathbf A^\top \;+\; \mathbf G\,\mathrm{var}_u\,\mathbf G^\top \;+\; \mathbf Q_{\mathrm{add}}\ }
$$

with $\mathbf A=\partial \mathbf x'/\partial\mathbf x$ (state-transition Jacobian, $24\times24$), $\mathbf G=\partial\mathbf x'/\partial[\delta\mathbf v,\delta\boldsymbol\theta]$ (input-noise Jacobian, $24\times6$), and $\mathrm{var}_u=\operatorname{diag}(\sigma_{\delta v}^2,\sigma_{\delta v}^2,\sigma_{\delta v}^2,\sigma_{\delta\theta}^2,\sigma_{\delta\theta}^2,\sigma_{\delta\theta}^2)$, $\sigma_{\delta\theta}=\Delta t\cdot$`EKF2_GYR_NOISE`, $\sigma_{\delta v}=\Delta t\cdot$`EKF2_ACC_NOISE`.

**Block structure.** Partition the state into a *dynamic* group $\mathbf x_d=[\mathbf q,\mathbf v,\mathbf p]$ (10) and a *slowly-varying* group $\mathbf x_s=[\mathbf b_{\delta\theta},\mathbf b_{\delta v},\mathbf m_I,\mathbf m_B,\mathbf w]$ (14). Because the latter are modelled as random walks (identity transition):

$$
\mathbf A=\begin{bmatrix}\mathbf A_{dd} & \mathbf A_{ds}\\[2pt] \mathbf 0_{14\times10} & \mathbf I_{14}\end{bmatrix},\qquad
\mathbf G=\begin{bmatrix}\mathbf G_{d}\\[2pt] \mathbf 0_{14\times6}\end{bmatrix}.
$$

**Dynamic sub-block $\mathbf A_{dd}$** ($10\times10$, rows/cols $[\mathbf q,\mathbf v,\mathbf p]$):

$$
\mathbf A_{dd}=\begin{bmatrix}
[\Delta\mathbf q]_R & \mathbf 0_{4\times3} & \mathbf 0_{4\times3}\\[4pt]
\dfrac{\partial(\mathbf R\,\delta\mathbf v_t)}{\partial\mathbf q} & \mathbf I_3 & \mathbf 0_3\\[8pt]
\mathbf 0_{3\times4} & \Delta t\,\mathbf I_3 & \mathbf I_3
\end{bmatrix}.
$$

**Coupling sub-block $\mathbf A_{ds}$** ($10\times14$) â€” only the bias columns are non-zero (the quaternion couples to the gyro-bias, the velocity to the accel-bias):

$$
\mathbf A_{ds}=\left[\begin{array}{c|c|c|c|c}
-\tfrac12\,\boldsymbol\Xi(\mathbf q) & \mathbf 0_{4\times3} & \mathbf 0_{4\times3} & \mathbf 0_{4\times3} & \mathbf 0_{4\times2}\\[4pt]
\mathbf 0_{3} & -\mathbf R & \mathbf 0_{3} & \mathbf 0_{3} & \mathbf 0_{3\times2}\\[4pt]
\mathbf 0_{3} & \mathbf 0_{3} & \mathbf 0_{3} & \mathbf 0_{3} & \mathbf 0_{3\times2}
\end{array}\right]
\quad\text{(cols: }\mathbf b_{\delta\theta},\mathbf b_{\delta v},\mathbf m_I,\mathbf m_B,\mathbf w\text{)}.
$$

**Input-noise sub-block $\mathbf G_d$** ($10\times6$, cols $[\delta\mathbf v,\delta\boldsymbol\theta]$):

$$
\mathbf G_d=\begin{bmatrix}\mathbf 0_{4\times3} & \tfrac12\,\boldsymbol\Xi(\mathbf q)\\[4pt] \mathbf R & \mathbf 0_3\\[4pt] \mathbf 0_3 & \mathbf 0_3\end{bmatrix}.
$$

**The sub-matrices.** With $\Delta\mathbf q=\Delta\mathbf q(\delta\boldsymbol\theta_c)=[\Delta q_0,\Delta q_1,\Delta q_2,\Delta q_3]^\top$, the right-multiplication matrix is

$$
[\Delta\mathbf q]_R=\begin{bmatrix}
\Delta q_0 & -\Delta q_1 & -\Delta q_2 & -\Delta q_3\\
\Delta q_1 & \Delta q_0 & \Delta q_3 & -\Delta q_2\\
\Delta q_2 & -\Delta q_3 & \Delta q_0 & \Delta q_1\\
\Delta q_3 & \Delta q_2 & -\Delta q_1 & \Delta q_0
\end{bmatrix},
$$

the quaternion kinematic matrix $\boldsymbol\Xi(\mathbf q)$ (from $\partial(\mathbf q\otimes[1,\tfrac12\boldsymbol\phi])/\partial\boldsymbol\phi$) is

$$
\boldsymbol\Xi(\mathbf q)=\begin{bmatrix}-q_1 & -q_2 & -q_3\\ q_0 & -q_3 & q_2\\ q_3 & q_0 & -q_1\\ -q_2 & q_1 & q_0\end{bmatrix},
$$

and the rotated-vector Jacobian (for $\mathbf a=\delta\mathbf v_t$), a $3\times4$ block, is

$$
\frac{\partial(\mathbf R\mathbf a)}{\partial\mathbf q}=2\left[\;q_0\mathbf a+\mathbf q_v\times\mathbf a \;\middle|\; \mathbf q_v^\top\mathbf a\,\mathbf I_3+\mathbf q_v\mathbf a^\top-\mathbf a\,\mathbf q_v^\top-q_0[\mathbf a]_\times\;\right],
$$

with $\mathbf R(\mathbf q)$ the simplified unit-quaternion DCM (`derivation_utils.py:56`)

$$
\mathbf R(\mathbf q)=\begin{bmatrix}
1-2q_2^2-2q_3^2 & 2(q_1q_2-q_0q_3) & 2(q_1q_3+q_0q_2)\\
2(q_1q_2+q_0q_3) & 1-2q_1^2-2q_3^2 & 2(q_2q_3-q_0q_1)\\
2(q_1q_3-q_0q_2) & 2(q_2q_3+q_0q_1) & 1-2q_1^2-2q_2^2
\end{bmatrix}.
$$

**Additive process noise $\mathbf Q_{\mathrm{add}}=\operatorname{diag}(\dots)$** for the random-walk states (`covariance.cpp:227-241`), zero on $\mathbf q,\mathbf v,\mathbf p$:

| States | diagonal entry | Param (default) | Gating |
|---|---|---|---|
| 10â€“12 $\mathbf b_{\delta\theta}$ | $(\Delta t^2\,\sigma_{g b})^2$ | `EKF2_GYR_B_NOISE` 1.0e-3 | frozen if `!GyroBias` |
| 13â€“15 $\mathbf b_{\delta v}$ | $(\Delta t^2\,\sigma_{a b})^2$ | `EKF2_ACC_B_NOISE` 3.0e-3 | frozen if `!AccelBias` âˆ¥ high-manoeuvre âˆ¥ bad-accel âˆ¥ axis clipping âˆ¥ not observable |
| 16â€“18 $\mathbf m_I$ | $(\Delta t\,\sigma_{mI})^2$ | `EKF2_MAG_E_NOISE` 1.0e-3 | only if `mag_3D` & $\sum P_{16:18}<0.1$ |
| 19â€“21 $\mathbf m_B$ | $(\Delta t\,\sigma_{mB})^2$ | `EKF2_MAG_B_NOISE` 1.0e-4 | only if `mag_3D` & $\sum P_{19:21}<0.1$ |
| 22â€“23 $\mathbf w$ | $\big[\sigma_w(1+0.5\lvert\dot h\rvert)\big]^2\Delta t$ | `EKF2_WIND_NSD` 1.0e-2 | only if `wind` & $\sum P_{22:23}<1$ |

**Bias inhibit** (`covariance.cpp:125-190`): unobservable or hard-manoeuvre axes ($\;\overline{\lvert\boldsymbol\omega\rvert}>$`acc_bias_learn_gyr_lim` âˆ¥ $\overline{\lVert\mathbf a\rVert}>$`acc_bias_learn_acc_lim`) have their bias variance *frozen* (saved/restored). `fixCovarianceErrors()` enforces symmetry/limits afterward.

### 5.3 Generic measurement update

Each aiding source builds an innovation/variance/test-ratio, then applies the Kalman update. Vel/pos/height use the **sequential scalar** helper `fuseVelPosHeight()` (`vel_pos_fusion.cpp:193`); others use the analogous `measurementUpdate()`/`fuse()` path:

$$
\mathbf y = \mathbf z - h(\hat{\mathbf x}),\qquad
\mathbf S = \mathbf H\mathbf P\mathbf H^\top + \mathbf R,\qquad
r = \frac{\mathbf y^2}{\gamma^2\,\mathbf S}\ \overset{?}{<}\ 1,
$$
$$
\mathbf K = \mathbf P\mathbf H^\top\mathbf S^{-1},\qquad
\hat{\mathbf x}\leftarrow\hat{\mathbf x}-\mathbf K\mathbf y,\qquad
\mathbf P\leftarrow\mathbf P-\mathbf K\mathbf H\mathbf P,
$$

where $\gamma$ is the per-sensor innovation gate. For a scalar vel/pos/height observation $\mathbf H=\mathbf e_s^\top$ (unit row at state $s$), so $\mathbf S=P_{ss}+R$ and $\mathbf K=\mathbf P_{:,s}/\mathbf S$ â€” exactly `Kfusion(row)=P(row,s)/innov_var` (`vel_pos_fusion.cpp:200`). A bad-vertical-accel case clamps (rather than rejects) the vertical innovation to ride out IMU clipping.

