### 6.2 Observation models $h(\mathbf x)$ and Jacobians $\mathbf H=\partial h/\partial\mathbf x$

Each $\mathbf H$ is **sparse** â€” non-zero only on the states a measurement touches. Below, the non-zero blocks are shown at their state indices; SymForce emits the fully-expanded scalar expressions in the generated headers (`derivation.py` is the symbolic source).

**Direct velocity / position / height** â€” unit selection rows:

$$
\mathbf H_{\mathbf v}=\big[\,\mathbf 0_{3\times4}\ \ \mathbf I_3\ \ \mathbf 0_{3\times17}\,\big],\qquad
\mathbf H_{\mathbf p_{NE}}=\big[\,\cdots\ \mathbf I_2\ (\text{cols }7,8)\ \cdots\,\big],\qquad
\mathbf H_{p_z}=\mathbf e_9^\top .
$$

**Magnetometer, 3-axis** (`predict_mag_body`, `derivation.py:198`): $h=\mathbf R^\top\mathbf m_I+\mathbf m_B$, fused sequentially per axis. Non-zero blocks at $\{\mathbf q,\mathbf m_I,\mathbf m_B\}$:

$$
\mathbf H_{\mathrm{mag}}=\left[\ \underbrace{\frac{\partial(\mathbf R^\top\mathbf m_I)}{\partial\mathbf q}}_{3\times4}\ \middle|\ \underbrace{\mathbf R^\top}_{3\times3}\ \middle|\ \underbrace{\mathbf I_3}_{3\times3}\ \right]\quad(\text{cols }0\!-\!3,\ 16\!-\!18,\ 19\!-\!21).
$$

**Magnetometer heading** (`compute_yaw_321`, `derivation.py:256`): $h=\operatorname{atan2}(R_{21},R_{11})$ (the 312 variant uses $\operatorname{atan2}(-R_{12},R_{22})$ near pitch $\pm\tfrac\pi2$). Non-zero only on $\mathbf q$: $\mathbf H_\psi=\partial h/\partial\mathbf q\ (1\times4)$.

**Magnetic declination** (`derivation.py:324`): $h=\operatorname{atan2}(i_y,i_x)$; non-zero on $\mathbf m_I$:

$$
\frac{\partial h}{\partial i_x}=\frac{-i_y}{i_x^2+i_y^2},\qquad \frac{\partial h}{\partial i_y}=\frac{i_x}{i_x^2+i_y^2}.
$$

**Airspeed** (`derivation.py:119`): $\mathbf v_r=[v_x-w_x,\,v_y-w_y,\,v_z]^\top$, $h=\lVert\mathbf v_r\rVert$. Non-zero on $\mathbf v$ (cols 4â€“6) and $\mathbf w$ (cols 22â€“23):

$$
\frac{\partial h}{\partial \mathbf v}=\frac{\mathbf v_r^\top}{\lVert\mathbf v_r\rVert},\qquad
\frac{\partial h}{\partial (w_x,w_y)}=\frac{-(v_x-w_x,\ v_y-w_y)}{\lVert\mathbf v_r\rVert}.
$$

**Synthetic sideslip** (`predict_sideslip`, `derivation.py:152`): $\mathbf v_{r,b}=\mathbf R^\top\mathbf v_r$, $h=\beta=(\mathbf v_{r,b})_y/(\mathbf v_{r,b})_x$; observation $\mathbf z=0$. Non-zero on $\{\mathbf q,\mathbf v,\mathbf w\}$.

**Optical flow** (`predict_opt_flow`, `derivation.py:338`): with range $d$ and $\mathbf v_b=\mathbf R^\top\mathbf v$,

$$
h=\begin{bmatrix}(\mathbf v_b)_y/d\\ -(\mathbf v_b)_x/d\end{bmatrix},\qquad \mathbf H_{\mathrm{flow}}\ \text{non-zero on }\{\mathbf q,\mathbf v\}.
$$

**GNSS yaw** (`derivation.py:388`): antenna vector $\mathbf a_b=[\cos\psi_o,\sin\psi_o,0]^\top$, $\mathbf a_e=\mathbf R\mathbf a_b$, $h=\operatorname{atan2}((\mathbf a_e)_y,(\mathbf a_e)_x)$; non-zero on $\mathbf q$.

**Drag** (`predict_drag`, `derivation.py:413`): $\mathbf v_{r,b}=\mathbf R^\top\mathbf v_r$ and, per body axis,

$$
h_{x,y}=\underbrace{-\tfrac12\rho\,c_d\,(\mathbf v_{r,b})_{x,y}\,\lVert\mathbf v_{r,b}\rVert}_{\text{bluff-body}}\ \underbrace{-\,c_m\,(\mathbf v_{r,b})_{x,y}}_{\text{rotor momentum}}
$$

with $\rho$ air density, $c_d$ from `EKF2_BCOEF_{X,Y}`, $c_m=$`EKF2_MCOEF`. $\mathbf H$ touches $\{\mathbf q,\mathbf v,\mathbf w\}$ but the Kalman gain is **restricted to the wind states** $w_x,w_y$ (`derivation.py:450/470`) â€” drag only corrects wind.

**Gravity** (`derivation.py:475`): predicted body-frame gravity $h=\mathbf R^\top[0,0,-g]^\top$, innovation against the normalised measured specific force $g\,\hat{\mathbf a}$; non-zero on $\mathbf q$ only â†’ a pure **tilt (roll/pitch) constraint**.

### 6.3 Deep dives

**Velocity / position / height** (`vel_pos_fusion.cpp`): scalar form of Â§5.3 with $\mathbf S=P_{ss}+R$. `updateVerticalPositionAidSrcStatus` builds $y=p_z-\text{obs}$, $\mathbf S=P_{99}+\max(0.01^2,\text{obs\_var})$. Several sensors can drive $p_z$; the dispatcher + bias estimators (Â§6.5) reconcile them.

**Magnetometer** (`mag_fusion.cpp`): $R_{\mathrm{MAG}}=\sigma_m^2$; `ComputeMagInnovInnovVarAndHx` yields the sparse $\mathbf H$ over $\{\mathbf q,\mathbf m_I,\mathbf m_B\}$, fused Xâ†’Yâ†’Z with per-axis conditioning checks. Heading-only mode uses `fuseYaw`. Mode select (`EKF2_MAG_TYPE`) in `mag_control.cpp`.

**GPS** (`gps_control.cpp:42`): velocity obs variance $\sigma_v^2=\max(\text{sacc},\text{gps\_vel\_noise})^2$ with the **vertical component inflated** $\times1.5^2$ (`:91-92`); horizontal position $\sigma_p=\max(\text{hacc},\text{gps\_pos\_noise})$, **capped at `pos_noaid_noise`** when GPS is the only horizontal aid (`:103-109`). GPS height (when `EKF2_GPS_CTRL` has the VPOS bit) runs through the height dispatcher with its own bias estimator; dual-antenna yaw via `gps_yaw_fusion.cpp`.

### 6.4 The specialised sources (one line each)

- **Airspeed** â€” fixed-wing; resets wind on first fusion; needs `EKF2_ARSP_THR > 0`.
- **Sideslip** â€” synthetic $\beta=0$; fused ~every 150 ms; bootstraps/holds wind.
- **Drag** â€” multirotor wind from body X/Y specific force; gain â†’ wind only.
- **Optical flow** â€” LOS rate vs $\mathbf v_b/d$ minus body rate; noise scaled by quality; couples to terrain for $d$.
- **Range finder** â€” height-above-ground; $R=(\text{range\_noise}+\text{range\_noise\_scaler}\cdot\text{range})^2$; `EKF2_RNG_CTRL` (0/1/2); conditional aiding limited by HAGL/velocity/tilt + kinematic check.
- **External vision** â€” NED or FRD pos/vel/yaw/height; `EKF2_EV_CTRL` bitmask; frame conversion + lever arm; non-reference pos/height get bias estimators.
- **Gravity** â€” tilt constraint from the accelerometer when $\lVert\mathbf a\rVert\approx g$; `EKF2_IMU_CTRL` GravityVector bit.
- **Aux velocity** â€” generic external NE velocity (landing-target).
- **Zero-velocity / zero-yaw** â€” pseudo-measurements at rest to bound drift and let accel-bias learn.
- **Fake position / height** â€” last-known constraints with `pos_noaid_noise` when no real aiding exists.

### 6.5 Height / position **bias estimators**

When several sources can supply height (or horizontal position), one is the **reference** and the others are reconciled to it via a scalar Kalman **bias** filter (`bias_estimator.cpp`, model $A=1$, $x_{k+1}=x_k+v$, $y=x+w$):

$$
\textbf{predict: }\ \sigma^2\leftarrow\sigma^2+\psi\,\Delta t,\quad \psi=(\texttt{EKF2\_*\_BIAS\_NSD})^2,\quad (\sigma^2\leftarrow\sigma^2+\underbrace{1000}_{\text{boost}}\psi\Delta t\ \text{if offset detected}),
$$
$$
\textbf{fuse: }\ S=\sigma^2+\max(0.01^2,R),\quad K=\frac{\sigma^2}{S},\quad r=\frac{(\,z-b\,)^2}{\gamma^2 S},\quad b\leftarrow b+K(z-b),\quad \sigma^2\leftarrow(1-K)\sigma^2 .
$$

All four NSDs (baro/gps/rng/ev) default 0.13. The **reference sensor's bias estimator is inert** â€” `HeightBiasEstimator::predict/fuseBias` are guarded by `(_sensor_ref != _sensor)` (`height_bias_estimator.hpp:57/64`); the reference owns the datum, only non-reference offsets are tracked. *Offset detection*: $\lvert\mathrm{LPF}(\operatorname{sign}\cdot r)\rvert>0.2$ or persistent same-sign innovations (>10 s). Worked example (`EKF2_HGT_REF=0`, baro reference + GPS height): see `ekf2_height_ref_baro_2026-05-21.*`.

### 6.6 EKFGSF_yaw â€” emergency yaw (`EKFGSF_yaw.cpp`)

A bank of $N$ lightweight AHRS+EKF filters seeded at different yaw angles, weighted by a Gaussian-Sum likelihood from GPS-velocity consistency. On main-filter yaw divergence the confident composite $\hat\psi_{\mathrm{gsf}}$ **resets** the main EKF yaw. Published as `yaw_estimator_status`.

