## 7. Outputs

### 7.1 Output predictor (`output_predictor.cpp`)

The EKF solution is at the *delayed* horizon; the output predictor produces the low-latency *now* solution. Two phases.

**Forward INS â€” `calculateOutputStates()` (`:168`, every full-rate IMU sample):**

$$
\begin{aligned}
\delta\boldsymbol\theta_c &= \delta\boldsymbol\theta - \mathbf b_{\delta\theta} + \boldsymbol\delta_{\theta}^{\mathrm{corr}} & \text{(complementary correction term)}\\
\mathbf q_o &\leftarrow \big(\mathbf q_o\otimes\Delta\mathbf q(\delta\boldsymbol\theta_c)\big)/\lVert\cdot\rVert\\
\Delta\mathbf v_e &= \mathbf R(\mathbf q_o)\,(\delta\mathbf v-\mathbf b_{\delta v}),\quad \Delta v_{e,z}\mathrel{+}=g\,\delta t\\
\mathbf v_o &\mathrel{+}=\Delta\mathbf v_e,\qquad \mathbf p_o\mathrel{+}=\tfrac12(\mathbf v_o+\mathbf v_o^{-})\,\delta t\\
\mathbf v_{\mathrm{imu}} &= (\delta\boldsymbol\theta_c/\delta t)\times\mathbf r_{\mathrm{imu}} & \text{(lever-arm, â†’ NED)}
\end{aligned}
$$

**Complementary correction â€” `correctOutputStates()` (`:242`, once per EKF update):** push $\mathbf{out}_{\mathrm{new}}$ to a ring buffer, take the oldest (delayed) entry, drive it toward the EKF state:

$$
\mathbf q_{\mathrm{err}}=\big(\mathbf q_{\mathrm{EKF}}^{-1}\otimes\mathbf q_{o,\mathrm{delayed}}\big)/\lVert\cdot\rVert,\qquad
\boldsymbol\delta_a=\mp2\,[\,q_{\mathrm{err},1},q_{\mathrm{err},2},q_{\mathrm{err},3}\,]^\top,
$$
$$
k_{\mathrm{att}}=\frac{0.5\,\overline{\delta t}_{\mathrm{upd}}}{\tau_{\mathrm{delay}}},\quad
\boldsymbol\delta_\theta^{\mathrm{corr}}=k_{\mathrm{att}}\,\boldsymbol\delta_a;\qquad
k_v=\frac{\delta t}{\mathrm{clamp}(\tau_v,\delta t,10)},\ \ k_p=\frac{\delta t}{\mathrm{clamp}(\tau_p,\delta t,10)},
$$
$$
\mathbf c_v=\mathbf e_v\,k_v+\Big(\textstyle\sum\mathbf e_v\Big)k_v^2\,(0.1),\qquad
\mathbf c_p=\mathbf e_p\,k_p+\Big(\textstyle\sum\mathbf e_p\Big)k_p^2\,(0.1),
$$

applied as constant corrections across the buffer history. $\tau_v,\tau_p$ are `EKF2_TAU_VEL`/`EKF2_TAU_POS` (both 0.25 s); the $\mp$ sign tracks the shorter quaternion path. The attitude gain auto-adjusts with the delay to hold a damping ratio $\approx0.7$.

