## 8. EKF selector & runtime noise adaptation

![EKF2Selector scoring and failover](ekf2_estimator_pipeline_2026-05-25_selector.svg){width=100%}

### 8.1 EKF2Selector (`EKF2Selector.cpp`)

One EKF2 instance runs per IMU/mag set; the selector promotes one to publish the system topics.

- **IMU fault accumulators** (`UpdateErrorScores`, `:151`): per sensor, $\textstyle\sum(\text{inconsistency}-\text{threshold})\,\Delta t$ for gyro (threshold `EKF2_SEL_IMU_RAT` 7Â°/s; fault if $>$ `EKF2_SEL_IMU_ANG` 15Â°) and accel (`EKF2_SEL_IMU_ACC` 1 m/sÂ²; fault if $>$ `EKF2_SEL_IMU_VEL` 2 m/s).
- **Per-instance score** (`:298-356`): $\text{combined}=\max\!\big(\tfrac12(\text{vel\_tr}+\text{pos\_tr}),\ \text{hgt\_tr}\big)$; $\text{relative}\mathrel{+}=(\text{combined}_i-\text{combined}_{\mathrm{sel}})$ clamped to $\pm1$; healthy $=$ (no fault) $\wedge\ \text{combined}>0$; warning $=\text{combined}\ge1$.
- **Selection / failover** (`SelectInstance`, `:114`): health hysteresis (~1 s); switch to a better instance once it wins by `EKF2_SEL_ERR_RED` (0.2); **instant** switch on IMU fault/timeout; relative scores reset on switch. The winner republishes `vehicle_attitude/local_position/global_position/odometry/wind` + `sensor_selection`; `estimator_selector_status` reports scores. Single-EKF builds skip this.

